  <description type="morphology">Stem scales  brown.  Leaves  3--15 cm.  Petiole  chestnut brown, 0.50--0.75 mm diam.  Blade  deltate, 3--5-pinnate proximally, somewhat herbaceous, abaxially covered by whitish farina, adaxially glabrous or sparsely glandular; rachis rounded to slightly flattened adaxially.  Pinna costae  straight or nearly so, branches not arising from prominent angles.  Ultimate segments  not articulate, dark color of stalks continuing into segment bases abaxially; segment margins recurved, often partially concealing sporangia; veins often visible adaxially.  Sporangia  submarginal, borne on distal 1/3 of secondary veins, containing 64 spores. 2 n  = 54.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Sporulating summer--fall.</description>
